<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-057-207 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 277 263</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 18 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Western Digital says Amstrad suit unfounded.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>McCormick, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Western Digital Corp. (Cases)Amstrad Consumer Electronics PLC (Cases).andO;Ticker:    WDC.andO;Topic:     Law SuitDisk drives.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>WESTERN DIGITAL SAYS AMSTRAD SUIT UNFOUNDED 09/18/91 IRVINE, CALIFORNIA,U.S.A., 1991 SEP 18 (NB) -- Western Digital maintains that it has beeninformed of, but not yet legally served with, papers concerning a suit byBritish computer maker Amstrad Plc, which alleges that disk drives suppliedby Western Digital did not meet specifications, causing massive financiallosses.andM;Saying that out-of-spec drives caused many of the company's problems, Amstradis charging that Western Digital's failure to meet specifications cost theBritish company $3 million in direct expenses and $38 million in lostprofits.andP;  The company is also claiming $100 million in damages to Amstrad'sreputation for loss of good will.andM;Western Digital has said that, contrary to Amstrad's allegations, the drivesdid meet specifications.andP;  The company also points out that this suit involvesdisk drives initially shipped in 1988, so Amstrad did not make any claimsthat the drives did not meet specifications until 18 months after the firstshipment.andM;Western Digital says that it will not only fight the charges but willinvestigate the possibility of filing its own suit against Amstrad forextraordinary costs it incurred attempting to help Amstrad resolve itsproblems.andM;In an unusual twist, Amstrad is specifically claiming that the WesternDigital drives did not meet the same high-quality standards as Tandon drivesalso supplied to Amstrad.andP;  The problem for the court to decide will becomplicated because Western Digital says that the drives actually shipped toAmstrad were, in effect, Tandon drives of a design that Western acquired whenit purchased Tandon's disk drive operations in March of 1988.andM;Amstrad is a major British maker of low-cost computers for thr home market.andM;(John McCormick/19910918/Press Contact: Robert L. Erickson, Western Digital,914-932-7822)</TEXT></DOC>